Paper: hep-th/0102152

Date: 2001-02-22

Title: Geometry and Toplogy of Solitons

Authors: Nematollah Riazi

Comments: 44 pages. submitted to Int. J. Theor. Phys. Nonlin. Op. Group Theor

Basic concepts and definitions in differential geometry and topology whichare important in the theory of solitons and instantons are reviewed. Manyexamples from soliton theory are discussed briefly, in order to highlight theapplication of various geometrical concepts and techniques.